data.enText: to make a connection between people or things in your mind

data.chText: 一闻到烘烤食物的味道我就想起了童年。
data.enText: I always associate the smell of baking with my childhood.

data.chText: 在公众的心目中，他总是和恐怖电影紧密联系在一起。
data.enText: He is closely associated in the public mind with horror movies.
to spend time with sb, especially a person or people that sb else does not approve of

data.chText: 我不喜欢你和那些人混在一起。
data.enText: I don't like you associating with those people.
to show that you support or agree with sth

data.chText: 我可以公开表示赞成首相的话吗？
data.enText: May I associate myself with the Prime Minister's remarks? (= I agree with them)
of a lower rank, having fewer rights in a particular profession or organization

data.chText: 欧洲联盟的非正式会员身份
data.enText: associate membership of the European Union

data.chText: 准会员；副导演 / 主编

data.enText: joined to or connected with a profession or an organization

data.chText: 在日本的一家联营公司

data.enText: a person that you work with, do business with or spend a lot of time with

data.chText: 准学士（获得两年制高校学位）
data.enText: a person who has an Associate's degree (= one that is given after completing two years of study at a junior college)

simple_means.memory_skill: as 加强 + soci 社会 + ate 使… → 成为一个社会 → 联合

means: 准学士(获得两年制高校学位)

ex.chText: 你能说出我们在非洲的主要贸易伙伴之一吗？
ex.enText: Can you name one of our principal trading partners in Africa?

ex.chText: 他是我生意上的合伙人。
他更愿意和自己的另一半谈谈他的烦心事。
ex.enText: He prefers to discuss his worries with his partner.
She is my table tennis partner.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，词义广泛，可指有合作关系的组织或国家、生意上的合伙人、配偶或情人、跳舞或玩游戏的搭档等。

ex.chText: 他是总统最亲密的盟友之一。
ex.enText: He was one of the President's closest allies.
She described him as a close friend and an ally.

ex.chText: 如果你要在这个工作上成功，你就需要支持者。
ex.enText: If you're going to succeed in this job, you will need allies.

ex.chText: 欧洲同盟国会议是在哪里举行的？
ex.enText: Where did the meeting of the European allies take place?

synonyms.bx: 尤指向从政者提供支持的人，或同意在战争中给予另一国家支持和帮助的国家。

ex.chText: 吉姆是汤姆的一个生意伙伴。
ex.enText: Jim is one of Tom's business associates.

ex.chText: 我的同事庞特比较善于揣摩心理。
ex.enText: My associate Pont is psychologically more adept.

ex.chText: 与董事长关系密切的一位同事否认了他患癌症的报道。
ex.enText: A close associate of the chairman denied reports that he had cancer.

synonyms.bx: 指生意上的合作伙伴或一起工作的人。

tr: a degree granted by a two-year college on successful completion of the undergraduates course of studies
any event that usually accompanies or is closely connected with another
example: first was the lightning and then its thunderous associate

tr: a person who joins with others in some activity or endeavor
example: he had to consult his associate before continuing

tr: a person with subordinate membership in a society, institution, or commercial enterprise
example: associates in the law firm bill at a lower rate than do partners

tr: a friend who is frequently in the company of another
make a logical or causal connection
example: I cannot connect these two pieces of evidence in my mind
I cannot relate these events at all

tr: bring or come into association or action
example: The churches consociated to fight their dissolution

value.boxr_value: The verb is pronounced /ə'səʊsieɪt/. The noun and adjective are pronounced /ə'səʊsiət/. 动词读作/ə'səʊsieɪt/，名词和形容词读作/ə'səʊsiət/。

value.def: If you associate someone or something with another thing, the two are connected in your mind.

example.ex: Through science we've got the idea of associating progress with the future...
example.tran: 通过科学我们知道了应该把进步和未来联系起来。

example.ex: Rap groups have been barred from large musical events because they are associated with vandalism.
example.tran: 说唱组合被禁止参加大型的音乐活动，因为他们使人联想到肆意破坏公共财产的行为。

value.def: If you are associated with a particular organization, cause, or point of view, or if you associate yourself with it, you support it publicly.

example.ex: I haven't been associated with the project over the last year...
example.tran: 我去年一直没有参与那个项目。

example.ex: The press feels the need to associate itself with the green movement.
example.tran: 媒体感到有必要支持绿色运动。

value.tran: 使与（某个组织、事业或观点）有关系;公开支持

value.def: If you say that someone is associating with another person or group of people, you mean they are spending a lot of time in the company of people you do not approve of.

example.ex: What would they think if they knew that they were associating with a murderer?...
example.tran: 如果他们知道自己正在与一个杀人犯为伍会怎么想?

example.ex: They disapproved of her dancing at discos and associating with homosexuals.
example.tran: 他们不同意她在迪斯科舞厅跳舞并和同性恋鬼混。

value.def: Your associates are the people you are closely connected with, especially at work.
Associate is used before a rank or title to indicate a slightly different or lower rank or title.

example.ex: Mr Lin is associate director of the Institute...
example.tran: 林先生是研究所的副所长。

example.ex: She applied for associate membership last year.
example.tran: 她去年申请成为准会员。

value.tran: （用于等级或头衔前，表示稍有不同或略低）副的，准的
